@mburhanpurkar You're right, the documentation does not appear to be correct. For a input of size `(B, C, 128, 128, 128)` and J=3, L=5, B=2, C = 3, I also get `(B, C, 10, 6, P)`, and with J=3, L=3, `(B, C, 10, 3, P)`.  

@eickenberg are you able to shed some light on this? 

`standard` and `local` were removed, don't know if it happened at the time of your question. Could have been during the 2021 hackathon.
